In SDL_mixer, you can check if `Mix_OpenAudio()` has been successfully called and the audio has been opened by checking the return value of the function. 

The `Mix_OpenAudio()` function returns 0 on success and a negative value on failure. Therefore, you can use this return value to determine if the audio has been opened successfully.

Here's an example:

```cpp
if (Mix_OpenAudio(44100, MIX_DEFAULT_FORMAT, 2, 2048) < 0) {
